messages.subject: Re: [Unschooling-Discussion] Re: dinosaurs (SOMEONE ASKED ABOUT STATE DINO'S)
messages.msgSnippet: Hi, I believe it was on this list that someone asked about Dino bones found in each state (I guess, whether or not they have been, and what type).  I forgot
messages.messageBody:
Hi,

I believe it was on this list that someone asked about Dino bones found in
each state (I guess, whether or not they have been, and what type). I forgot
that I had this site bookmarked. It isn't the "official" (LOL, although, now
that I look at it closer, it says it is--it's put out by Enchanted Learning,
which seems to be a really reliable, great site) one that Deborah in IL sent, but
it is one more that you could bookmark. It seems pretty close to the one
Deborah sent, but it also seems to be geared to younger kids.

<A HREF="http://www.enchantedlearning.com/subjects/dinosaurs/dinofossils/locations/Statedinos.shtml">Official State Dinosaurs - Enchanted Learning Software</A>

Tracy



We forfeit three-fouths of ourselves in order to be like other people.

~Arthur Schopenhauer~
